text: `adult` data set contains questionnaire data _Adult_ database (originally called _Census Income_ Database) formatted data.frame.

title: Adult Data Set — adult
text: `adult` data.frame `r data(adult); nrow(adult)` rows `r data(adult); ncol(adult)` columns. See details. AGE numeric vector. WORKCLASS factor levels `Federal-gov`, `Local-gov`, `Never-worked`, `Private`, `Self-emp-inc`, `Self-emp--inc`, `State-gov`, `Without-pay`. FNLWGT numeric vector EDUCATION ordered factor levels `Preschool` < `1st-4th` < `5th-6th` < `7th-8th` < `9th` < `10th` < `11th` < `12th` < `HS-grad` < `Prof-school` < `Assoc-acdm` < `Assoc-voc` < `-college` < `Bachelors` < `Masters` < `Doctorate`. EDUCATIONNUM numeric vector. MARITALSTATUS factor levels `Divorced`, `Married-AF-spouse`, `Married-civ-spouse`, `Married-spouse-absent`, `Never-married`, `Separated`, `Widowed`. OCCUPATION factor levels `Adm-clerical`, `Armed-Forces`, `Craft-repair`, `Exec-managerial`, `Farming-fishing`, `Handlers-cleaners`, `Machine-op-inspct`, `-service`, `Priv-house-serv`, `Prof-specialty`, `Protective-serv`, `Sales`, `Tech-support`, `Transport-moving`. RELATIONSHIP factor levels `Husband`, `--family`, `-relative`, `-child`, `Unmarried`, `Wife`. FACE factor levels `Amer-Indian-Eskimo`, `Asian-Pac-Islander`, `Black`, ``, `White`. SEX factor levels `Female` `Male`. CAPITALGAIN numeric vector. CAPITALLOSS numeric vector. HOURSPERWEEK numeric vector. NATIVECOUNTRY factor levels `Cambodia`, `Canada`, `China`, `Columbia`, `Cuba`, `Dominican-Republic`, `Ecuador`, `El-Salvador`, `England`, `France`, `Germany`, `Greece`, `Guatemala`, `Haiti`, `Holand-Netherlands`, `Honduras`, `Hong`, `Hungary`, `India`, `Iran`, `Ireland`, `Italy`, `Jamaica`, `Japan`, `Laos`, `Mexico`, `Nicaragua`, `Outlying-US(Guam-USVI-etc)`, `Peru`, `Philippines`, `Poland`, `Portugal`, `Puerto-Rico`, `Scotland`, `South`, `Taiwan`, `Thailand`, `Trinadad&Tobago`, `United-States`, `Vietnam`, `Yugoslavia`. ABOVE50K binary integer (0/1) mentioning whether INCOME 50K .

Method used derive `nbins` buckets continuous explanatory variables. naming_conventions boolean - default TRUE. means certain naming convention respected. useNA Two values possible : "ifany" "". default,  package option "ifany". value "ifany" takes consideration missing values . value "" take consideration missing values case. verbose - boolean (default FALSE). TRUE information displayed console. useful using package big data. dec - integer : number decimal numeric variable. default, value 2. order_label character - option output order used plot function. parameter can take following values: "auto": numeric variable, order alphabetic. categorical variable, order count "alpha": order alphabetic "count": order decreasing number observations class "props : order decreasing proportion second value target "means : order decreasing target mean (continuous target) cont_target_trim numeric (default 0.01). continuous targets, desirable trim extreme values computing WOE. trimming factor percentage (0: trim <1). bxp_factor (default) 1.5 continuous target, coefficient used compute boxplot whiskers. num_as_categorical_nval (default: 5). variable less num_as_categorical_nval distinct values, considered used categorical numeric. autoguess_nrows - integer (default 1000). Numbers rows used guess variables types. Special value 0 provided rows used. woe_alternate_version character. Specify context WOE alternate definition used See vignette  methodology. Possible values 'if_continuous' (default) 'always'. woe_shift numeric (default) 0.01. Shifting value WOE computation prevent issues one bucket contains 0% 100% target. binary target, people also propose use 0.5. woe_post_cluster boolean (default FALSE). WOE computed, cluster values see  adequate group together modalities/buckets. Clusters used graphics. See vignette methodology. woe_post_cluster_n integer (default: 6). woe_post_cluster TRUE, number clusters used. smart_quantile_by numeric, binning method 'smart', quantile step - default y step 0.01. ... additional parameters (might used targeter functions, special side effect user).

title: targeter — targeter
text: function returns list class "targeter". list composed following elements: dataname - name analyzed dataset. description_data text description data target - name target. target_type - Target type, one autoguess (default) / binary / numeric / categorical (text expended "b" also works binary) description_target text description target analysis - name analysis. date - date analysis. profiles : list elements containing result individual crossing per variable. See crossvar class documentation.
